solutions.content:
What is actually generators ?

In javascript generators are the functions which have special functionality, they can pause and resume during execution. (We define generator function with the help of special syntax , `function * generatorFunctionName() { }`)

Understand with the help of example -
```
function* generatorFunction() {
  console.log('Execution started');
  yield 1;
  console.log('After first yield');
  yield 2;
  console.log('After second yield');
  yield 3;
  console.log('Execution completed');
}

const generator = generatorFunction(); // Creating an instance of the generator

console.log(generator.next()); // Output: { value: 1, done: false }
console.log(generator.next()); // Output: { value: 2, done: false }
console.log(generator.next()); // Output: { value: 3, done: false }
console.log(generator.next()); // Output: { value: undefined, done: true }
```
When we call `generatorFunction()` it will not execute the function, instead of this it will return a generator object, which have `next` method, by calling next method we can resume the execution of generator.
When function see yield in function it will stop the execution and return the object which have to fields which store the yield value and done state of the function.

We can say we use next method to resume the execution of generator function and use yield keyword to pause the execution.
# Code
```
var fibGenerator = function*() {
    let a = 0;
    yield a;
    let b = 1;
    yield b;
    while(true){
        const fibNumber = a + b;
        a = b;
        b = fibNumber;
        yield fibNumber;
    }
};
```

