 When a function is marked as a generator using the  function* syntax, it can use the yield keyword to produce a value that can be retrieved by the caller. 

The generator function will pause its execution at the yield statement and return the value specified in the statement to the caller. The generator function can then be resumed by calling the next() method on the generator object.


