# Approach
* First traverse the matrix by 2 for loops and check if any element of matrix is not zero then call dfs function in which we are calculating sum of connected elements.....
* Then we make an isvalid function in which we checked that whether the index where we traverse is valid or within the bound or not....
* if yes then return true else false.....
* Then in dfs function we add elements in sum variable if connected and make that element 0 so that we can't traverse it again and then call dfs recursively if element connected or valid....
* conditions in dfs are:-
    1. first we check for row+1 and col
    2. second we check for row-1 and col
    3. third we check for row and col+1
    4. last we check for row and col-1
* in last we return sum in dfs function.....
* at last in findMaxFish function we take the maximum value of sum among all and return the same.........

---


- [Time complexity: $$O(MN)$$]()

---


- [Space complexity:$$ O(1)$$]()

---


