# Intuition
We shouldn't add 1 on 2 siblings since it's better to add 1 to the parent.

# Approach
From leaf to root, for each pair of siblings (x, y), keep the larger value as the result. And the we need to add the difference to the smaller value to make (x, y) the same. And add the same value to the parent since the parent is the "new leaf".

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {        
public:
    int minIncrements(int n, vector<int>& cost) {
      int r = 0;
      for (int i = n - 1; i; i -= 2) {
         r += abs(cost[i] - cost[i - 1]);
         cost[(i - 1) >> 1] += max(cost[i], cost[i - 1]);
       }
       return r;
    }
};
```

