# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For a particular node its children should have equal path sum.
So we will calculate path sum of both childs and make them equal. And we will perform this operation for all nodes. 
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
First we will traverse using dfs from starting node and calculate path sum of childs. Our dfs(node) will return path sum. After finding path sum of childs difference of both paths will be added to our final answer and then we return path sum till parent node.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) -> Traversing complete tree using dfs.
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(log(n)) -> Stack size during recursion call
