# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

This is an idea based on recursion but we do use bottom up approach. The idea here is to solve for subtrees and update the variable **ans** After solving for subtree we update its cost (By solving i mean we have calculated the no of operations to make all path sums in that subtree equal) and update it so that we do not need to calculate the path sum again and again. This has to be done from lower nodes to upper nodes.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

We are given an array representing a tree.
We do not solve for leaf nodes since the path sum to leaf from that node is its value only.

- For each non-leaf node, we get the leaf-path-sum from its left node and right node.
- We calculate the diff and this would the operations required to make them equal
``` 
ans += abs(rightCost - leftCost)

```
- update the child with less sum to become equal to its sibling.
- Update the sum of the node to either **curr + leftCost** or **curr + rightCost** since both would be equal.
- 
