solutions.content:
I originally solved by restoring the array, assuming we start either from `0` or `1`.

Then, I realized that we can simplify the check - we can always build the array if we have an even number of `1`.

## One-Liner
**C++**
```cpp
bool doesValidArrayExist(vector<int>& derived) { 
    return accumulate(begin(derived), end(derived), 0, bit_xor<>()) == 0;
}
```

## Original Solution
**C++**
```cpp
bool check(vector<int>& derived, int i, int start, int cur) {
    if (i + 1 == derived.size())
