Nice warmup problem, we can get it done by using a reading pointer `r` we will advance from the back up to the first position which is not a `'0'`; we will then resize `num` to be `r + 1` character and `return` it.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string removeTrailingZeros(string num) {
        // support variables
        int r = num.size();
        // moving r to the last non-'0' digit
        while (num[--r] == '0');
        // pruning the zeroes (if any) out of num
        num.resize(r + 1);
        return num;
    }
};
```

