# Approach
The function takes an input obj, which can be either an array or an object.

It first checks whether the input obj is an array using the Array.

isArray(obj) method. If it is an array, it directly returns true if the array's length is 0, indicating that the array is empty.

If the input obj is not an array (i.e., an object), it proceeds to the else block and converts the object's values into an array using Object.values(obj).

It then checks whether the array's length is 0. If it is 0, it means the object has no properties and is considered empty, so the function returns true.

If the array's length is not 0, it means the object has properties, and the function returns false, indicating that the object is not empty.

