**intuition: Suppose we are making the number zero after x number of operations. means we are subtracting nums2 x times from nums1. so the remaining number i.e nums1-x*nums2 must be expressible as sum of x powers of two.**

for eg:- nums1=20 and nums2 =7;

first we check 20-(1*7)=14 . Is 14 expressible as sum of powers of 2 having only one number in the series? No.

20-(2*7)=6 . as 6 can be expressed as 2^2+2^1; so we got 2 as the ans;

for positive numbers we can check until nums1- cnt*(nums2) is >0 and for negative numbers we can simply do 60 operations to cross check;

upvote if you like it



class Solution {
public:

    int popcount(long long n) {
        std::bitset<64> bits(n);
         return bits.count();
    }
    bool dos(long long n, int x) {
        return x<=n && x>=popcount(n);
    }
    int makeTheIntegerZero(int num1, int num2) {

        if(num2==0){
            for(int i=1;i<32;i++){
                if(dos(num1,i)){
                    return i;
                }
            }
        }else if(num2>0){

            int cnt=1,idx=1;
            while(true){
                if(num1-cnt*num2<0){
                    return -1;
                }else{
                    if(dos((long long)(num1-cnt*num2),idx)){
                        return idx;
                    }
                    cnt++;
                    idx++;
                }
            }
        }else{
            long long cnt=1;
            int idx=1;
            for(int i=0;i<=60;i++){

                long long par=cnt*num2;

                if(dos((long long)(num1-par),idx)){
                    return idx;
                }else{
                    cnt++;
                    idx++;
                }
            }
        }
        return 0;
    }
};

