Why greater than equal to m?
When *i<sub>1</sub> ,i<sub>2</sub>, i<sub>3</sub> ..... i<sub>m</sub>* all will be choosen to 0 then X will be.** 

**X = (2<sup>0</sup> + 2<sup>0</sup> + 2<sup>0</sup> + ....+ 2<sup>0</sup>)**

