# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
If you observe, if there are total `n`steps, the additions should be such that:
`sum(n powers of 2 (diff or same)) = nums1-n*nums2`. 

This is the only observation needed. Either this difference should have exactly `n`different powers of 2 or if the different powers are less than `n`, we can break a bigger power of 2 into two or more powers to reach `n`.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(60*32)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(60)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

