# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have to find the number of steps at which the condition stated below must be satisfied.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We have to make `num1 == 0`. Suppose `num1` will become `num1 == 0`, then previously `num1 = num2 + 2^i1 + num2 + 2^i2 + ..... + num2 + 2^ik`. Simplify this we get `num1 = k*num2 + (2^i1 + 2^i2 + .... + 2^ik)` or `num1 - k*num2 = (2^i1 + 2^i2 + .... + 2^ik)`

# Complexity
