# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach

<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

1. if num1 < num2, answer is -1;

2. if answer = N, then: num1 - N * (2^i + num2) = 0 or
num1 - N * num2 = N * 2^i
2^i is the number with one bit. N * 2^i is the number from N (if i = 0) to some number with N bits(or less, because if we take 4 and 4 it will be 1 bit)
So at each iteration we will substract num2 from num1 and check these conditions
3. we need to use long, because num2 can be < 0 and num1 will increase


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(logN)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
