# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Before choosing an element `nums[i]`, all we need to know is, what is `the maximum score` before `index i`. For this we can use **Dynamic Programming**.

For every element `nums[i]`, we have two choices:
1. **Take `nums[i]`:** While taking the element, there can be two cases. The maximum score can come from odd parity or the even parity of the previous index. Also the parity changes to `nums[i] & 1`.
2. **Skip `nums[i]`:** The parity remains the same.

---

### Solving a smaller subproblem first
`x = 6`, `nums = [3, 2]`

In the following table, let's concentrate on  `element 2` at `index 1` for now. We'll dive into the scores of 3 a bit later (base cases).

| ``nums``        | 3  | 2                             |
|-----------------|----|-------------------------------|
| 0 (even parity) | -4 | score: `max(2 + (-4), 2 + 3 - 6) = -1` |
| 1 (odd parity)  | 3  | score: `3`                    |

### Observations:
- When we take $2$, it is in the even parity. The score changed in two ways: from the even parity of the previous index, $2 + dp[i - 1][0]$ and from the odd parity which will include $x=6$ score deduction, $2 + dp[i - 1][1] - 6$.
- When we skip $2$, the parity doesn't change. So we're still in the odd parity and the score will settle from $dp[i - 1][1]$.

---

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
### State
`dp[i][parity]` states the maximum score upto *index i* for the respective even-odd parity.

### Transitions
- take:
    sameParity `dp[i - 1][parity] + nums[i]`
    changingParity `dp[i - 1][parity ^ 1] + nums[i] - x`
`dp[i][parity] = max(sameParity, changingParity)`
- skip: `dp[i][parity ^ 1] = dp[i - 1][parity ^ 1]`

### Base Cases
- `dp[0][parity] = nums[0]`
- `dp[0][parity ^ 1] = nums[0] - x`

### Final Subproblem
- `max(dp)`

---

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

---


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long maxScore(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<vector<long long>> dp(n, vector<long long> (2, 0));

        bool parity = nums[0] & 1;
        dp[0][parity] = nums[0];
        dp[0][parity ^ 1] = nums[0] - x;

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            bool parity = nums[i] & 1;
            long long takeSame = dp[i - 1][parity] + nums[i];
            long long takeDiff = dp[i - 1][parity ^ 1] + nums[i] - x;
            dp[i][parity] = max(takeSame, takeDiff);
            dp[i][parity ^ 1] = dp[i - 1][parity ^ 1];
        }

        long long ans = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            ans = max({ans, dp[i][0], dp[i][1]});
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

