# Intuition
Given that we initially have `nums[0]`, for next `nums[ind]` we can either `take` or `not take` , just a simple knapsack variant.

# Approach
If we take the curr ind we have to check the parity of curr , compared to prev `p`, if its the same we dont have to subtract any thing , if they are diff we just subtract `x`. Choose the max of the two.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)
- Space complexity:
O(N) or O(100005*2)
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
long long dp[100005][2];
    long long maxScore(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        return solve(nums, x, 0, nums[0] % 2);
    }

    long long solve(vector<int>& nums, int x, int ind, int p) {
        if (ind >= nums.size()) {
            return 0;
        }
        if(dp[ind][p]) return dp[ind][p];
        long long dontTake=solve(nums,x,ind+1,p);
        long long takeScore = nums[ind]+solve(nums,x,ind+1,nums[ind]%2);
        if (nums[ind] % 2 != p) takeScore -= x;

        return dp[ind][p]=max(takeScore,dontTake);
    }
};

```

