Hello fellow Leetcoders, this contest was my first 4/4 ever. After grinding every day for the past 3 months, I think the practice is finally paying off. Here is my solution for this problem. I hope it helps. :>

Basically, we go through each index carrying the information of the parity of our previous value. 1 == odd, 0 == even. We penalize accordingly when we take index i. :>

```python
class Solution:
    def maxScore(self, nums: List[int], x: int) -> int:
        n = len(nums)

        @lru_cache(None)
        def dp(i, prev):
            if i == n:
                return 0

            skip = dp(i + 1, prev)
            take = nums[i] + dp(i + 1, nums[i] % 2)
            if prev % 2 != nums[i] % 2:
                take -= x
            return max(skip, take)

        return nums[0] + dp(1, nums[0] % 2)
```

