# Approach
Since you can go to any index $j>i$ then the only thing that matters is the best odd/even answer since we only decrease the score in case of different parity. So it is only necessary to have those max values and finally return the one that matches $nums[0]$.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$O(n)$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long maxScore(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        int n = nums.size();
        long long maxEven = 0,maxOdd = 0;

        for(int i = n-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(nums[i]&1)
                maxOdd = max(maxOdd+nums[i],maxEven+nums[i]-x);
            else
                maxEven = max(maxEven+nums[i],maxOdd+nums[i]-x);
        }

        if(nums[0]&1)return maxOdd;
        return maxEven;
    }
};
```

