# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have two option for each element, either we can go to that position or we can skip that. So, it is looking similar to 0-1 Knapsack.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can simply create recursive function to calculate both the posibilities and will pick the maximum one. For memoizing we need to create a Table of size n * 2 (as parity is changing from 0 to 1).

For parity, Created a variable "temp" to store both the posibilites accordingly.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n*2) => O(n);
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
- Space complexity: O(n*2) => O(n);
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector< vector<long long>> T;

    long long solve(vector<int>& nums, int &x, int i, int par){
        if(i >= nums.size()){
            return 0;
        }

        int temp = 0;
        if(nums[i]%2 == par){
            temp = nums[i];
        }else{
            temp = nums[i] - x;
        }

        if(T[i][par] != -1){
            return T[i][par];
        }

        long long choose = temp + 0ll + solve(nums, x, i+1, nums[i]%2);
        long long nope = solve(nums, x, i+1, par);

        return T[i][par] = max(choose, nope);
    }

    long long maxScore(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        int n = nums.size();
        T = vector< vector<long long>> (n+1, vector<long long>(2, -1));

        return nums[0] + 0ll + solve(nums,x,1,nums[0]%2);
    }
};
```

