we will use 2d dp to store values at a particular index and parity(even/odd) as score depends on these 2 only(dp[i][j[--> i for index and j for parity) . Then we will recursively call the function. Here are 3 cases
> If we don't take we just move ahead and parity remains same as well as nothing is added
>if parity of current no. and prev no. is same just add that no. and parity remains same
>if parity of current no. is different we will add that no. as well as subtract 'x' from it as stated in question and change the parity to parity of current no. for future calculation

